ABOARD NANCHANG DESTROYER, Oct. 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Russian navies wrapped up their first joint maritime cruise on Saturday. A ceremony was held in the eastern part of the East China Sea before the two fleets departed. The joint cruise kicked off on Oct. 17 after the "Joint Sea-2021" exercise that started on Oct. 14. During the seven-day cruise, a combined ship formation conducted drills of joint navigation, joint maneuver and practical use of weapons. Enditem